<p>I have written an ant task for my automated deployment.</p>  <pre><code>    &lt;target name="deployWMBComponent"&gt;     &lt;for list="${esb.ci.WMB.deployment.target.brokers}" param="brokername" delimiter=" "&gt;         &lt;sequential&gt;                            &lt;for list="${esb.ci.WMB.deployment.target.egs}" param="egname" delimiter=" "&gt;                   &lt;sequential&gt;                             &lt;exec executable="cmd.exe" failonerror="true" logerror="true" append="true" vmlauncher="false" dir="${esb.ci.WMB.dp.home}"&gt;                         &lt;arg value="/C" /&gt;                         &lt;arg value="mqsiprofile.cmd &amp;amp;&amp;amp; mqsideployscript.bat" /&gt;                         &lt;arg value="-n" /&gt;                         &lt;arg value="${brokerConfigFilePath}\@{brokername}.broker" /&gt;                         &lt;arg value="-e" /&gt;                         &lt;arg value="@{egname}" /&gt;                         &lt;arg value="-w" /&gt;                         &lt;arg value="600" /&gt;                         &lt;arg value="-a" /&gt;                         &lt;arg value="${barLocalPath}" /&gt;                                                                              &lt;/exec&gt;                 &lt;/sequential&gt;             &lt;/for&gt;         &lt;/sequential&gt;     &lt;/for&gt;       &lt;/target&gt; </code></pre>  <p>All the properties are defined in a property file. I'm adding a new boolean parameter, <code>Default_Propagation</code>, if its <code>TRUE</code> the above mentioned script should call another ant task, if <code>FALSE</code> the above script should execute directly.</p>